Threat intelligence
Threat Intelligence (TI) is the process of collecting, analyzing, and using information about cyber threats to help organizations protect themselves.
Key Elements:
Data Collection - from malware, logs, phishing, dark web, etc.
threat Analysis - who is attacking, how ,and why
Actionable Information - helps security teams take preventive steps

Main Types of Threat Intelligence:

Strategic - Big-picture trends, geopolitical risks - Executives, managers

Tactical - Attacker tools and techniques (TTPs) - Blue Teams, defenders

Operational - Info about real-time attacks - SOC analysts

Technical - IPs, malware hashes, URLs, IOCs - Engineers, systems

Why is TI important?
It helps organizations stay one step ahead of attackers by detecting threats before they cause damage.
